[ESTABLISHED] A flake input in a `flake.nix` file cannot have a `description` attribute inside its input attribute set. 

If you include a `description` attribute inside a flake input, such as:
```nix
infernal-init = {
  url = "github:lowcache/infernal-init";
  description = "custom repo";
  inputs.nixpkgs.follows = "nixpkgs";
};
```
Nix will fail to evaluate the flake and return the following error:
```
error: unexpected flake input attribute 'description'
```

The `description` attribute is only supported at the top level of the flake attribute set itself (as a sibling to `inputs` and `outputs`) to describe the current flake, but not within individual dependency definitions in `inputs`.

